title.narrative: Production forests whose management has been transferred to the private sector

comment.narrative: All public forests are currently managed by KFS, no management responsibility ha s been transferred to the private sector.

title.narrative: Area of forests in project intervention areas managed according to approved forest management plans.

comment.narrative: Management plans are outdated or not available, forest harvesting banned

title.narrative: Community/User groups collaborating with GoK institutions in water and/or forest activities (% of which members are female)
Implementation of KFS Strategic Plan activities supported

comment.narrative: The KFS Strategic Plan is a five-year document (FY 2010 to 2014), outlining 120 activities under six strategic objectives.

title.narrative: Sub-projects implemented to improve livelihoods in Upper Tana Catchment

comment.narrative: Following field verification, only 197 of the 249 initially approved passed, thus the number of sub-projects implemented went downby 52.
Lower Nzoia design delayed, KfW reiterated its interest to co-finance, construction anticipated to be carried out under theproposed Water Security and Climate Resilience Project.
This comprises (i) Mwea with 9,150 has and (ii) Bunyala with 270 has (part of the new Lower Nzoia Scheme).
Mwea rehabilitation works advancing according to schedule.

title.narrative: Area provided with irrigation and drainage services

comment.narrative: Works in Mwea advancing, L. Nzoia design further delayed (due to quality issues contract has been terminated and procurement ofnewconsultant underway). Construction will not be financed under NRMP.
